tjc.model.agent

Class Agent

  • java.lang.Object
    • tjc.model.agent.Agent

  • public class Agent
extends java.lang.Object
    The agent class stores the information about a given agent and contains functions to manage the power plants held within it.

      • updateDataTax

        public void updateDataTax(int tick,
                          DataManager dataManager)
        Updates the agent for a tick when running on a tax system. Shows a warning if the agent has already been updated for the current tick, sorts the held power plants based on revenue for the current tax rate and puts them in descending order. Iterates through the power plants, generating electricity until the required amount is reached. Removes power plants who have been inactive for too long.
        Parameters:
        tick - The current tick to update for
        dataManager - The dataManager that stores the information for the model

      • decideBid

        public int decideBid(float value,
                     float portionComplete)
        Decide on whether to put in a bid for a given value. The maximum value to offer is calculated based off the income per carbon unit for the current most efficient unused power plant. This is also weighted by the portion of credits left unused relative to the portion of the agents goal power generation.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to accept or reject
        portionComplete - The portion of credits remaining
        Returns:
        The number of credits to buy at the given value

      • useCredits

        public void useCredits(int number,
                       DataManager dm)
        Use credits to run a power plant. Show an error if the number of credits being used is out by more than 1 from the required credits to run the current best power plant
        Parameters:
        number - The number of credits
        dm - The data manager to pass through to usePower

      • setUnused

      • sortPowerNormalised

        public void sortPowerNormalised()
